FBIS3-16757 "drsov054_b_94013" FBIS-SOV-94-054 Document Type:Daily Report 20 Mar 1994 RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS Political Issues Further on Yeltsin Activities in Sochi Supports Sochi as Olympics Candidate LD2003135694 Moscow 2x2 Television in Russian 1330 GMT 20 Mar 94 LD2003135694 Moscow 2x2 Television Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Text] Russian President Boris Yeltsin has supported the idea of holding the 2002 Olympic games in Sochi. Having acquainted himself with a plan connected to putting forward the town as a candidate, he noted that the planned sports facilities can be used after the Olympics.
